==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stamping
<hw>Stamp"ing</hw>, <def><pos>a. & n.</pos> from <er>Stamp</er>,
<pos>v.</pos></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stamping ground</b></col>, <cd>a place frequented, and
much trodden, by animals, wild or domesticated</cd>; hence
(<mark>Colloq.</mark>), <cd>the scene of one's labors or exploits; also,
one's favorite resort; in this sense, often called <altname>stomping
ground</altname>.</cd> <mark>[U.S.]</mark> -- <col><b>Stamping
machine</b></col>, <cd>a machine for forming metallic articles or
impressions by stamping.</cd> -- <col><b>Stamping mill</b></col>
<fld>(Mining)</fld>, <cd>a stamp mill.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stance</ent>⟦br⟧
